article.description: — Jalen Johnson had 16 points as Mercer narrowly defeated Coastal Carolina 74-69 on Monday night.
article.headline: Johnson leads Mercer past Coastal Carolina 74-69
article.linkText: Johnson leads Mercer past Coastal Carolina 74-69
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — Jalen Johnson had 16 points as Mercer narrowly defeated Coastal Carolina 74-69 on Monday night. James Glisson III had 16 points for the Bears (6-4), who have won four in a row. Felipe Haase added 13 points. Kamar Robertson had 12 points. Vince Cole had 17 points for the Chanticleers (4-3). Wilfried Likayi added 15 points. Ebrima Dibba had 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
